Sime Darby Plantation Sdn Bhd Key Developments

Sime Darby Plantation Sdn Bhd Reports Unaudited Earnings and Production Results for the Second Quarter Ended December 31, 2016
Feb 27 17
Sime Darby Plantation Sdn Bhd reported unaudited earnings and production results for the second quarter ended December 31, 2016. Profit before interest and tax was MYR 568 million against MYR 159 million a year ago. This was mainly due to higher average CPO price realised and better FFB production especially in Indonesia and Papua New Guinea. 


FFB production for the quarter was 4.873 million MT against 5.427 million MT a year ago. The lower FFB production was due to the reduction in mature hectares as the division accelerates its replanting exercise with better planting materials.


